AN ACT making an appropriation to the University of Nevada,
Reno, for a technology initiative for certain students; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. There is hereby appropriated from the State
2 General Fund to the University of Nevada, Reno, the sum of
3 $2,400,000 to carry out an initiative for the purchase, distribution
4 and maintenance of tablet computers for the use of each student who
5 is:
6 (a) Enrolled at the University of Nevada, Reno, during the 2025-
7 2027 biennium; and
8 (b) Is eligible to receive a federal Pell Grant pursuant to 20
9 U.S.C. § 1070a, based on the eligibility requirements and awarding
10 rules in effect on December 31, 2024, as increased or decreased for
11 Fiscal Year 2025-2026 and Fiscal Year 2026-2027, respectively, in
12 an amount corresponding to the percentage of increase or decrease
13 in the Consumer Price Index (All Items) published by the United
14 States Department of Labor for the preceding fiscal year.
15 2. Upon acceptance of the money appropriated by subsection 1,
16 the University of Nevada, Reno, agrees to:
17 (a) On or before February 1, 2027, prepare and transmit a report
18 to the Director of the Legislative Counsel Bureau for transmission to
-
