1 the Senate Standing Committee on Finance and the Assembly
2 Standing Committee on Ways and Means of the 84th Session of the
3 Nevada Legislature. The report must include, without limitation, as
4 of December 31, 2026:
5 (1) The number of students who participated in the initiative
6 set forth in subsection 1;
7 (2) An evaluation of the effectiveness of the initiative in
8 improving the academic performance of the students who
9 participated in the initiative;
10 (3) A summary of the statistics relating to usage of the
11 technology provided pursuant to the initiative; and
12 (4) An itemization of the use of the money appropriated by
13 subsection 1.
14 (b) Prepare and transmit a report to the Interim Finance
15 Committee on or before September 17, 2027, that describes each
16 expenditure made from the money appropriated by subsection 1
17 from the date on which the money was received by the University of
18 Nevada, Reno, through June 30, 2027.
19 3. Any remaining balance of the appropriation made by
20 subsection 1 must not be committed for expenditure after June 30,
21 2027, by the entity to which the appropriation is made or any entity
22 to which money from the appropriation is granted or otherwise
23 transferred in any manner, and any portion of the appropriated
24 money remaining must not be spent for any purpose after
25 September 17, 2027, by either the entity to which the money was
26 appropriated or the entity to which the money was subsequently
27 granted or transferred, and must be reverted to the State General
28 Fund on or before September 17, 2027.
29 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective upon passage and approval.
